  "prompt": "What are the best schools in Hyderabad for 8th class?",
  "response": "Hyderabad is home to several reputable schools that offer quality education for students in the 8th class. While the best school can vary based on individual preferences, here are some of the well-regarded schools in Hyderabad known for their academic performance, infrastructure, extracurricular activities, and overall reputation:\n\n1. **Hyderabad Public School (HPS)** - This school has multiple branches and is known for its strong academic curriculum and extracurricular programs.\n\n2. **Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan** - Offers a robust curriculum along with a focus on cultural education and extracurricular activities.\n\n3. **Chinmaya Vidyalaya** - Known for integrating traditional values with modern education. The school emphasizes holistic development.\n\n4. **Oberoi International School** - This school follows the IB curriculum and is known for its global approach to education.\n\n5. **International School of Hyderabad (ISH)** - An internationally recognized school that focuses on an inquiry-based learning approach and offers both IB and Cambridge curricula.\n\n6. **Sreenidhi International School** - Offers a variety of curricula, focusing on a holistic approach to education and comprehensive extracurricular options.\n\n7. **Gitanjali School** - Known for its academic excellence and various programs aimed at skill development.\n\n8. **Silver Oaks International School** - Offers a combination of Indian and international curricula, and emphasizes value-based education.\n\n9. **Delhi Public School (DPS) Hyderabad** - With a strong emphasis on academics and extracurriculars, DPS is a popular choice among parents.\n\n10. **St. Andrews School** - Known for a strong academic program combined with various co-curricular options.\n\nWhen choosing a school, it\u2019s important to consider factors such as the curriculum offered, faculty qualifications, campus facilities, extracurricular activities, and the school\u2019s philosophy and values. It\u2019s advisable to visit the schools, talk to faculty, and understand their approach to education before making a decision.",
